				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">The Only Reason I Play EverQuest --&gt; Bard :)<a name="52489"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 18 04 6:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Greetings All,
<br />

<br />
This is my first post on this wonderful forum!  I love the website, and I am excited to get to know many of you who frequent this forum.  My name is Ashlii, I am a Bard of the 24th Song on the Morden Rasp server, and I am addicted to EverQuest.
<br />

<br />
I am here to learn from you all because knowledge can be attained from anyone, despite their level.  There are so many little short-cuts and things you learn through out the years that you wish you knew back when you first started a bard.  I have played EverQuest since 1999, however I took a 3 year vacation after being called a Petless Mage.  I was a Wizard thinking I'd be omnipotent and the best compared to all others at higher levels.
<br />

<br />
I have read most of the information on the site and I am considered a valuable asset to any group I make or join.  I know there is much to learn still, and that is why I am going to make a big effort to get all the information I can out of you all.  The newest thing I've learned recently was the /gems game.  I might have heard of it years ago, but the first time I ever played that game was a few days ago.  Heh, its neat stuff like that that makes me smile.  Here are a few problems I am having, sure I could search the entire web and site for it to see if it has ever been answered, but I would like to hear it from your mouth.  Only answer if you would like to help, thank you in advance <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
1.  How important is the defense skill to us as bards?  I would think it would be Very important.  Well, I have only like *blushes* 12 points in defense and I am wondering if its possible to raise it still at a much higher level?  Can I just let green mobs hit me all day to raise it or can only stuff I melee (blue/white/yellow/red) raise my defense?
<br />

<br />
((Sidenote to #1:  I maxed my 1h slash skill, however I noticed when I tried to max my very low 1h blunt and piercing skills, it was almost impossible at higher levels.  I had to raise the skills through a trainer in order to begin to raise it by attacking mobs in my experience range.))
<br />

<br />
2.  Mordern Rasp server prices on items are ridiculously high compared to any other server.  This means when I buy equipment and weapons, I better be 100% sure that the item is the best item in comparison to other similar items.  I have spoken to countless Bards of All Levels, and it seems that the most important stats on items seems to be in order of importance:  Charisma, Armor Class, Dexterity, Agility, then Health Points or Stamina
<br />

<br />
My question is, do you agree this should be the method to see if the item is Best suited for you?  I love to group, and my main problem is magic resistance.  I noticed the Singing Armor has some effects for level 45+ I believe, but most of the armor has little or no statistical benefit in comparison to other equipment.  A Singing Breastplate on Morden Rasp goes for 50,000 platinum.  Similar Singing armor pieces go for 5,000pp.  Ridiculous prices for items that I see little benefit from.  My main concern is the order of importance for stats on equipment, so please direct your attention to that, thank you.
<br />

<br />
3. Now I may have overlooked this in another post or guide, but I think an updated answer is needed anyways just in case someone has a new or different opinion on this.  All opinions are greatly appreciated, thank you!  What are the 3 general types of songs do you play during battle?  I know this will be answered on a case per case basis, however I want to point out a specific event that has troubled me:
<br />
--
<br />
We're fighting in a dungeon and the puller pulls too many mobs.  Perhaps 2 or 3.  Now, I have the choice to keep playing my 3 songs consisting of Group Haste/Str buff, AC/MR Increase, Heal Song or I can try to Mez one of the mobs.  Do you keep playing the songs or try to Mez?  Is it possible to constantly Mez multiple mobs While fighting?  Is it possible to Charm multiple mobs?  while fighting?
<br />

<br />
Thanks for any input, I truly appreciate your time and reply.
<br />

<br />
Sincerely,
<br />
Ashlii of the 24th Song
<br />
</span></td>
