			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The Only Reason I Play EverQuest --&gt; Bard :)<a name="52499"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 18 04 10:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Welcome to the community first of all
<br />
1. yes the only way to raise defence is to get smacked around by exp mobs. The same thing goes for weapon skills if you need to raise a weapon skill I suggest you get a fast weapon for that skill and get some dex buffs and again need exp mobs for it to work.
<br />

<br />
2. The way I went was cha,dex,int,ac, sta,hp  The reason for this was I loathed missed notes as well as the fact I kept having to play enchanter alot in my groups. The stats people choose will vary by their playstyle though.
<br />

<br />
3. ok you can only charm one mob at a time, second of all if its only one add that you need to mez what you can do with practice is target the to be mezed mob start the mez toggle back to orginal target and continue to attack it.
<br />

<br />
As bards we only get 1 line of sight check during casting so this allows us to effect mobs we have targeted at the start of a song rather then the target we have at the end of it.
<br />

<br />
This will take practise but once you have the pattern right you will learn to continue your twist semi normally with a mob mezed in camp. Learning skills like these is often what makes you standout as a bard compared to the ones that people make as pocket mana sources.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">“Allow my song to heal your wounds, clear your mind, and hasten your blade”

