			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Thanks<a name="52500"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 18 04 10:15 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Your question regarding what you would do it a certain situation revolves around what role(s) you are playing in your group. For example, if there is no enchanter in your group, you take control of CC meaning yes, you should mez, charm, do whatever you have to in order to make things easier for other members of your group. You can only charm 1 thing at a time and you can't sing another charm until your orginal breaks (not even on your current charm).  Since bards are very good pullers it would be wise for you to get your defense up! At times your lull/pull combo won't work exactle textbook and you'll get 2-3 mobs on you. For that brief time they'll beat on you and if you have low Def, well, you might have a short life because mobs will crank you for all you're worth with defense as low as yours at that lvl. PLUS, you will not gain skill against green mobs so please dont think you can let a decaying skelly beat on you and expect to gain skill hehe.
<br />

<br />
For myself, i like to focus on getting some +cha items but i don't overlook the other stats either. I try to find something that will balance my points out nicely. I understand that at higher lvls maxing stats through items is a lot easier.
<br />

<br />
I find that setting up a key for &quot;toggle between mobs&quot; especially useful when it comes to crowd control. Sometimes through the frenzy you can't exactly get a bead on where the h*ll your mouse pointer is and even then you might just constantly click on a party member. With the key set (you get it in your options menu, not setting up a hotkey) you can easily go through mobs nearest you. I hope this little bit helps.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
