				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi Shassiash,
<br />

<br />
I anticipated that someone would disagree with me, and of course, it's a matter of opinion to a certain degree, however I would like to point out one small thing. It is the consensus that Dex has nothing to do with missed notes.  Here's an overly longwinded discussion on missed notes that may help shed some light on that subject.
<br />

<br />
http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessage?topicID=19312.topic
<br />

<br />
That leaves charisma as the determining factor behind missed notes, charm, mez &amp; lull.  You could easily argue that charisma is the most important bard stat, but it's this bards opinion that it's more important to live long enough to finish casting mez, than to have a high charisma so that it lands.  For the purpose of this guide, I'd suggest that if your torn between which stats to boost first, go for a balance, between hp, sta &amp; cha.  When I was a young bard I went for Cha first, and it worked well for me, but in retropsect I wish I had focused a bit more on HP, it would have saved me a lot of unnecessary upgrades. 
<br />

<br />
I hope I didn't confuse you too much with all that Ashlii.</span></td>
