				<td colspan="2"><span>As usual, lots of good advice from these folks.  I personally got my  Defense skill up by being the puller in most of my groups.  If you're pulling, at lower levels anyway, you will get hit, often, unless your MA is very good at grabbing agro as you enter the camp.  For weapon skills, you're DPS from melee is not tremendous, it never will be, so if you need to work on 1hb, put that mace in your main hand and put your 1hs in your off hand, I always put the weapon with the lowest associated skill in my main hand when in a group and in my secondary slot when soloing or when my dps was absolutely necessary.  You will eventually max out all of those skills.
<br />

<br />
Binding skills has been discussed so I won't go into that too much but I will remind you that your Sense Traps and Disarm Traps skills do NOT require the actual presence of a trap to get increases.  You can bind those skills to movement keys and then go swarm kiting and watch your skills max out quickly.
<br />

<br />
For equipment, I focues on Cha and Int when I was starting out, I soloed a lot and mobs rarely hit me so not missing notes and having a large mana pool were very important, more than the hp issue.  Now, I tend to group much more than I solo, I do lots of LDON's and lots of raiding and now AC and HP are king, I try to maintain and sometimes improve my current stats while always on the lookout for more hp, current goal is to have 100hp in every slot and I'm a little over halfway there, just shy of 4khp unbuffed and just over 1400AC, again unbuffed.  Not uber, but that's with NO elemental gear yet either.
<br />

<br />
Getting ahead of the game.  Specific questions that pertain to your current level can also be directed to the level specific forums on this site where you may get some better answers.
<br />

