				<td colspan="2"><span>Greetings Ashii -
<br />

<br />
I recently re-started my bard from level 22 and am now at 40, painlessly thanks to the fine folks here.  I would like to give you another option for binding your skills keys.  I have never used the macro key (it wasn't in-game when I took my break), so I found another way.  
<br />

<br />
Put your regular &quot;forage&quot; key in slot one on the ability menu.
<br />

<br />
Go into your social keys and scroll over to a blank one.  Right click one and name it (named mine Forage1) and assign a color to distinguish it from the regular forage key.
<br />

<br />
First line: &quot;/doability 1&quot;
<br />
Second line: &quot;/autoinventory&quot;
<br />

<br />
It may help to add a pause between the two because often the autoinventory is missed for me, but this makes it painless to forage.
<br />

<br />
Now, go into you keyboard options and assign forward movement to the &quot;w&quot; key and hotkey 10 to the &quot;w&quot; key.  Now, whichever button you put in slot 10 will activate everytime you move forward.  So, you can put in your sense trap, disarm, forage1, etc. and auto-skill.  
<br />

<br />
A word of advice when in ldon's:  use the forage1 skill in slot 10.  The items you forage in ldon's can be valuable and if you put sense traps, it will spin you around to look at the trap at inopportune times.  
<br />

<br />
The recently added ability to &quot;toggle target&quot; has helped me immensely with CC.  Coupled with &quot;cycle target&quot; you can always have anything targetted you wish with just a keystroke or two.
<br />

<br />
Also, consider using a gamepad for the hotkeys.  I hear several work, I use the Nostromo N52.  There are 14 hot-buttons on it that I use to control my 8 spells, 4 movement keys and targetting keys.  It has several other toys (like the ability to make any key repeat), as well as the ability to triple the uses for the hot-buttons.
<br />

<br />
This set-up works well for me and is highly customizable, maybe there is something here you can use.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
