				<td colspan="2"><span>Cool, I will have to try out /autoinventory when i get home tonight!  I had heard there was a way to do this, but no one I ever asked seemed to know how.
<br />

<br />
As far as defense, yes, very important as everyone else has said.  at level 24 you can get xp and raise it at the same time... paludal caverns, solo the fiends, they will be LB at level 24 i believe, so they won't thrash you, but will give you skill gains and xp, and happily as a bard their disease is of no concern, your regen song greatly overpowers it.  I solo'd the fiends until level 23 for decent xp (when I was bored and not grouped that is).  But I always had max defense, as i was a tank bard into my 50s.  I still tank for fun, but never in really tough places.
<br />

<br />
for stats... I started with all AC and str gear, it was cheap and since I was the main tank I felt str was important, I needed to hit the mobs a lot... now I regret my choice of str for all my starting points, but its ok.  There are probably even some old posts on this site where I argued for my choice, lol.  But in the end game you CAN max all your stats (I have not yet) so don't sweat it.  While you budget is small though, try and get decent AC while getting as much charisma as you can... a temperance costs 12pp, and lasts for quite a while, and give you 800 hps.  You would be hard pressed to buy 800hps worth of armor at an early level.  So get yourself some charisma, some dex, some AC, a temperance, and go kick butt.
<br />

<br />
lots of people already answered the question about mapping keys...  
<br />

<br />
And as for songs, I always twist haste, overhaste, regen, and an odd 4th song (usually either resists or more overhaste, but sometimes a levitate, or enduring breath, or a buff song, or something)  I also keep a lull, and a mez memmed, as well as at least one, if not 2 pulling songs. (2 because the requiem of time which is my normal pull song takes 18 seconds to reset, so if I mess up and double hit it when I didn't already have a song going I can switch to my other pull song without re-lulling everything <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> )</span></td>
