			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The Only Reason I Play EverQuest --&gt; Bard :)<a name="53208"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 22 04 10:10 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1.  Pulling and Crowd Controlling for groups is how I kept my Defense maxed.  What others said about getting hit by blue conned mobs is correct.  AGI is the primary stat for Defense skillups, so get an AGI buff whenever you can.
<br />

<br />
Snare Fear kiting (see kiting guides) is the best way I know to improve offensive weapons skills when they are lagging.  Get a nice DEX buff before you head out if you can.  What Zel said about which one in which hand is 100% on (of course).
<br />

<br />
2.  Gear:  The leading cause of death in EQ is lack of HP.  CHA is great.  The only things that are PROVEN about CHA, however, is that lots of it appears to reduce missed notes, and we KNOW that when a Lull gets resisted, it checks your CHA to see if the mob will aggro.  
<br />

<br />
Besides that, there is NO EVIDENCE OR PROOF whatsoever that CHA has any affect on resist rates or early breaking of mez or charm.  What most certainly DOES affect whether they will break early, is the MR debuff component of the song.  A MR check happens every tick to determine if it will break early.  EQUIP A FLUTE TO MAXIMIZE THE MR DEBUFF.  There is NOTHING more important than this for making sure your mezzes and charms stick.  And, imo, this is MUCH easier than maxing your CHA.
<br />

<br />
3.  Song selection is all based on what others in the group are doing.  Depending on the mobs you are fighting, the priorites for me are:  Slow, Regular Haste, Overhaste, Damage Shield, Regen.  Against dragons and other nasty casters, resists are most important, of course.  Basically, if the Shammy or Chanter is Slowing (theirs are usually better than ours), let em.  Same goes with regular haste.  You won't get &quot;overhaste&quot; (the stackable kind) until your 50s.
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure if anyone already gave you a CC guide or not.  But this post is kinda long, and I need a cup of coffee, so I will leave that part go for now.
<br />

<br />
Short answer:  You can mez up to three adds.  You can mez two, and throw in a third buff song.  When you are down to one add, you can keep it mezzed, and /assist the main tank.  Your &quot;Toggle last two targets&quot; and &quot;Cycle nearest NPC&quot; keys are essential to pulling this off.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=564823">Scherzo Glissando </a><BR>
Maestro, Molto Espressivo</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td height="2"></td>
			</tr><tr>
